<span id="Description"></span>
==Descrição==

The [[Image:Draft_Snap_Lock.svg|24px]] '''Draft Snap Lock''' command enables or disables snapping globally.

<span id="Usage"></span>
==Utilização==

For general information about snapping see [[Draft_Snap|Draft Snap]].

# To invoke '''Draft Snap Lock''' do one of the following:
#* Press the {{Button|[[Image:Draft_Snap_Lock.svg|16px]] [[Draft_Snap_Lock|Snap Lock]]}} button in the Draft Snap toolbar.
#* [[Draft_Workbench|Draft]]: Press the {{Button|[[Image:Draft_Snap_Lock.svg|x16px]][[Image:Toolbar_flyout_arrow.svg|x16px]]}} button (short click) in the [[Draft_Snap_Widget|Draft Snap Widget]]. {{Version|0.21}}
#* Draft: Hold down the {{Button|[[Image:Draft_Snap_Lock.svg|x16px]][[Image:Toolbar_flyout_arrow.svg|x16px]]}} button in the Draft Snap Widget and in the menu that opens select the {{MenuCommand|[[Image:Draft_Snap_Lock.svg|16px]] Snap Lock}} option.
#* [[BIM_Workbench|BIM]]: Select the {{MenuCommand|Snapping → [[Image:Draft_Snap_Lock.svg|16px]] Snap Lock}} option from the menu, or from the [[3D_View|3D View]] context menu.
#* Use the keyboard shortcut: {{KEY|Shift}}+{{KEY|S}}. If a command is active this shortcut only works if none of the input boxes in the task panel has the focus. {{Version|0.21}}
#* Use the "in-command" shortcut: {{KEY|S}}. This shortcut can only be used if a command is active and one of the input boxes in the task panel has the focus. It does not work for all commands.


